==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Meconin
<hw>Mec"o*nin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>m⟦eacute⟧conine</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A substance
regarded as an anhydride of meconinic acid, existing in opium and
extracted as a white crystalline substance. Also erroneously called
<altname>meconina</altname>, <altname>meconia</altname>, etc., as though
it were an alkaloid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Meconinic</ent>⟦br⟧
